{
  "doc_id": "13878",
  "text": "According to commonly held beliefs, women are more emotional, experiencing and expressing emotions in general more intensely than do men. They are also thought to have superiority in emotional competence such as understanding others' emotions [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . There is evidence from research using self-report and performance based measures that women have a better ability to identify and name their feelings than men even when controlling the effects of verbal intelligence, education, and socioeconomic status [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
